|MKBAdvanced Schemes: Notes Nobody Admits Dictating|000

Syntax:
  schemes [list]
  schemes info <name>
  schemes learn <name>
  schemes activate <name>
  schemes swap <active> for <learned>

Charlatan Rank opens one new scheme every five Ranks from 35 through 100.
Drina teaches each open scheme for gold and you permanently scribble its notes
inside your cloak. Learning automatically activates the scheme when an empty
slot is available. A learned, inactive scheme may fill a newly earned empty
slot for free; replacing an occupied slot costs gold.

One scheme may be active initially. Rank 50 opens a second active slot, Rank
100 opens a third, and every fifty Ranks thereafter opens another. By Rank
100 every scheme can be learned, but only three can be active.

  Rank 35   Hair Trigger
    Loading a weapon in combat immediately throws a carried elemental or acid
    flask at the current foe.

  Rank 40   Unstable Mixture
    Elemental flasks deal 20 percent less direct damage but leave Burning,
    Chilled, or lost concentration behind.

  Rank 45   Bad Batch
    Cookash gains two potency and loses one quarter of its duration. One batch
    in four reveals itself as the wrong colour when quaffed.

  Rank 50   Hot Merchandise
    Weapon loads last 50 percent longer and double their fitting side effect.

  Rank 55   Cut Product
    Stretch Poison leaves a second owner-bound weaker dose that preserves the
    source poison's unusual nastiness. Both coatings lose one strength.

  Rank 60   Loaded Question
    Successful Confuse blocks concentration for three extra seconds instead
    of fully paralyzing the mark.

  Rank 65   Second Story
    A resisted Confuse may still spoil concentration for two seconds.

  Rank 70   Improvised Exit
    Avoid breaks the current fight as it begins, but Fancy Footwork lasts half
    as long.

  Rank 75   Fine Print
    Red salt and blue mixer halve their immediate bonus and double their
    regeneration duration.

  Rank 80   Plausible Deniability
    Volatile flasks stop splashing their thrower and deal 30 percent less
    direct damage.

  Rank 85   Marked Cards
    Pocket Sand used on an already distracted mark exposes instead of blinds.

  Rank 90   False Bottom
    Carry two acid and two elemental flasks at once. Flasks brewed while the
    scheme is active lose one potency.

  Rank 95   Double Bluff
    Distract exposes a fooled mark instead of trying to end the fight.

  Rank 100  The Long Con
    An opening-powered Sucker Punch trades half its bonus burst for a longer
    Exposed condition.

Listing and inspecting schemes works anywhere. Drina must be present to teach,
activate, or swap cloak notes. She does not extend credit and denies ever
having seen your handwriting.
